      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "&quot;You should only catch an exception when you have a strategy for actually handling it&quot; -- I&#39;ll add that if you can add useful context to the exception&#39;s message, you should catch, wrap (including the additional context), and throw. Don&#39;t log -- leave that up to the code that actually handles it. A ConnectException, for example, becomes much more useful and actionable when paired with the name of the thing we were trying to connect to."
