      "creation_date" : 1694710308,
      "post_id" : 3495968,
      "comment_id" : 135930465,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "“Remember, though, that if all the exceptions belong to the same class hierarchy, you can simply catch that base exception type.” That’s only true with sealed inheritance."
